      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i keep getting a 500 error on our /api/v1/checkout/process endpoint whenever a user tries to apply a discount code. i've attached the partial logs below but it's super intermittent. can u see what's up?\n\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: Internal Server Error - RequestID: 8829-xf2\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] STACKTRACE: Unhandled exception in DiscountService.apply(DiscountObject dto)\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke \"com.store.models.Coupon.getExpiryDate()\" because \"coupon\" is null\n[2023-10-27 14:22:02] ERROR: Internal Server Error - RequestID: 8830-xf4\n[2023-10-27 14:22:02] STACKTRACE: Unhandled exception in DiscountService.apply(DiscountObject dto)\n[2023-10-27 14:22:02] java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke \"com.store.models.Coupon.getExpiryDate()\" because \"coupon\" is null",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The 500 errors are happening because the `Coupon` object is coming back as `null` when your code tries to access its `getExpiryDate()` method. This is a classic case of a logic gap where the discount code validation logic failed to retrieve the coupon details, likely due to a missing database record or a race condition in your caching layer.\n\nTo fix this, you need to ensure that the `Coupon` entity is never null before calling methods on it. You can add a defensive check in your `DiscountService.apply` method to handle the `NullPointerException` gracefully by returning a user-friendly error message instead of crashing the server.\n\nSince the issue is intermittent, it's possible that the coupon data is being fetched asynchronously and hasn't loaded yet at the exact moment the service tries to use it. I'd recommend adding a retry mechanism or ensuring your database transaction is properly committed before the service attempts to validate the expiry date.\n\nAlso, consider adding some logging around the retrieval of the coupon object to see exactly why it's null in those specific request IDs. You might want to log the user ID, the discount code used, and the timestamp to correlate it with your database audit logs.\n\nFinally, don't forget",
